<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10063312>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Soliella flava (Rathbun, 1894), male (NIO/BOD/AB/BRY/00004, 2.8 × 1.8 mm), eastern Arabian Sea, India: (A) dorsal habitus (preserved colour); (B) ventral habitus (preserved colour); (C) left cheliped fingers (disto-external view); (D) right P2 dactylar articulation, dorsal view; (E) male pleon, ventral view; (F) G1, pleonal view. Liomera monticulosa (A. Milne Edwards, 1873), male (NIO/BOD/AB/BRY/00005, 2.2 × 1.2 mm), eastern Arabian Sea, India: (G) dorsal habitus (preserved specimen); (H) ventral habitus (preserved specimen); (I) left cheliped, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–E, G–I, 1 mm; C–D, 0.5 mm; F, 0.1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10063312/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

